@startuml
title Cache Deployment - Backend Strategy

skinparam linetype ortho

node "CLI / Commands" as CLI {
  component "cache refresh/status/clear\n+ transform commands" as Commands
}

node "Application Runtime" as APP {
  component "UseCases + Stages" as Stages
  component "Role ports\n(cache contracts)" as Ports
  component "SqliteCacheGateway\n(namespaced lifecycle facade)" as SqliteGateway
}

node "Current Backend (canonical)" as CUR {
  database "SQLite" as SqliteDB
  component "Sqlite repositories\n(cache/identity/pending)" as SqliteRepos
}

node "Future backend option A" as FUT_A {
  database "PostgreSQL" as PgDB
  component "PgCacheGateway\n(planned)" as PgGateway
}

node "Future backend option B" as FUT_B {
  database "Redis" as RedisDB
  component "Redis adjunct runtime\n(ephemeral acceleration)" as RedisAdj
}

CLI --> Commands
Commands --> Stages
Stages ..> Ports
Ports <.. SqliteGateway

SqliteGateway --> SqliteRepos
SqliteRepos --> SqliteDB

Ports <.. PgGateway : same role contracts
PgGateway --> PgDB

RedisAdj --> RedisDB
Stages ..> RedisAdj : optional (non-canonical)

note bottom of APP
Canonical replacement for SQLite snapshot/search semantics:
PostgreSQL-like backend.
Redis is treated as adjunct/ephemeral acceleration,
not as drop-in replacement for full snapshot semantics.
end note

@enduml
